content:
Release tarballs are the preferred way to install Userli. This page explains how to create them. First, you&rsquo;ll need a Github API token. The token needs the following priviledges:
public_repo, repo:status, repo_deployment  Now, execute the following script. It will create a version tag, release and copy the info from CHANGELOG.md to the release info.
$ GITHUB_API_TOKEN=&lt;token&gt; GPG_SIGN_KEY=&quot;&lt;key_id&gt;&quot; ./bin/github-release.sh &lt;version&gt;
